{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01W2S6CLVXa9s4PFZKWPc4fd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the pods mount `cockroachdb-certs` as `/cockroach/cockroach-certs`. The verification command uses `--certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs`. So the actual working certs are in `cockroachdb-certs`.\n\nBut the verification checks `crdb-cluster-certs` for the cert fingerprint and validity. This seems like the task wants me to:\n1. Update `crdb-cluster-certs` with new 1-year certs\n2. Also update `cockroachdb-certs` so the running cluster keeps working\n3. Optionally patch the pods to use `crdb-cluster-certs` OR just update both secrets\n4. Perform a rolling restart of the CockroachDB pods to pick up the new certificates\n\nThe most straightforward approach is probably to generate fresh certs in the toolbox, update both secrets, and then restart the pods so they load the new credentials. I'll update both secrets with the new certificates and then trigger a rolling restart of the StatefulSet to pick them up. Before I do that though, I should verify whether the client certificate also needs rotation or if it's separate from the node cert rotation process.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1218,"cache_read_input_tokens":31437,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1218},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5584a478-d99e-4919-8ac1-94a851f842be","uuid":"56eaa9ed-aaa4-4a13-b7ab-3c66f375dda1","request_id":"req_011Cc9Z4rXqTB4WjSH2CbenN"}
